title: Northgate, ECHS, Trinity compete in ASICS Invitational
text:
Northgate, ECHS, Trinity compete in ASICS Invitational Wednesday, October 14, 2015 
Northgate's girls and boys cross country teams turned in solid performances Saturday in the Championship Division of the Alexander/ASICS Invitational. 
The Lady Vikings finished 11th, while the Northgate boys were 12th. 
Elise Glorvigen (19:54) led the way for the Lady Vikings with a 33rd-place performance. Caroline Nelson (20:25) was 46th, Erica Lee (21:37) was 87th, and Sydney Tuttle (21:55) was 99th. 
In the Championship boys division, Hayden Hasberger (16:29) was 27th, Andrew Tuttle (16:48) was 50th, Sherman Dewey (17:07) was 68th, Jaelin Rainey (17:28) was 85th and Alex DiTaranto (18:41) was 148th. 
East Coweta's boys were 12th in the 5A-6A race, while the Lady Indians were 15th. 
Matthew Shumake (17:52) finished 31st to lead the Indians. Bobby Martin (18:34) was 73rd and Xavier Church (18:54) was 94th. Miya Dean (22:14) lead the Lady Indians with a 49th place finish. Holy Hind (23:16) was 88th and Haley Davis (23:23) was 92nd. 
In the Class AAAA-A division, the Trinity girls finished eighth, while the boys were ninth. Hans Troyer was 20th (17:40), Jacob Richardson (17:55) was 27th and Adam Aycock (18:16) was 42nd to lead the Lions. Faith Robertson(22:40) led the Trinity girls with a 26thplace finish. Kayleigh Sherrod (22:49) was 30th and Emily Olson (22:55) was 32nd. More
